# zKCNT POS Project Conventions

## Tech Stack
- Frontend: Nuxt 3 (Vue 3) with Tailwind CSS v4, SSR disabled (SPA/PWA)
- Local DB: Dexie.js (IndexedDB wrapper)
- Backend: PocketBase v0.38 (SQLite-backed, single binary)
- Containerization: Docker with separate dev/prod compose files
- Task Runner: go-task (`Taskfile.yml` at project root)
- Package Manager: Bun (`bun.lock`, not npm)

## Development Workflow
- Use `task` commands to run the project — prefer `task local` for daily dev
- Frontend: always use **Bun** (`bun install`, `bun run dev`, `bun run build`) — never npm
- Local mode: PocketBase in Docker + Bun frontend on host (`task local`)
- Full Docker dev: `task dev` | Production: `task prod`
- When adding a new Docker Compose service, update `Taskfile.yml` accordingly
- Lockfile: commit `bun.lock`, do not commit `package-lock.json`

## Architecture: Offline-First + Multi-Tenant

### Multi-Tenant Pattern
- Every business data collection MUST have a `store` relation field
- All queries MUST filter by the active store ID
- PocketBase API rules MUST verify store membership via `store_members`
- Dexie compound indexes: `[store+field]` for store-scoped queries

### Offline-First Pattern
- All reads go through Dexie.js (local cache) first
- Online writes: PocketBase first, then sync to Dexie
- Offline writes: write to Dexie + add to `syncQueue`
- On reconnect: drain sync queue, then pull remote changes
- Conflict resolution: last-write-wins using `updated` timestamp

## Directory Structure (Nuxt 4 compat mode)
```
frontend/
├── app/                    # Nuxt app directory
│   ├── assets/css/         # Tailwind CSS
│   ├── components/         # Vue components (auto-imported)
│   ├── composables/        # use*.ts composables (auto-imported)
│   ├── layouts/            # Layout templates
│   ├── lib/                # Non-auto-imported utilities
│   │   ├── db.ts           # Dexie database
│   │   ├── types/          # TypeScript interfaces
│   │   └── sync/           # Sync engine
│   ├── middleware/          # Route middleware
│   ├── pages/              # File-based routing
│   └── plugins/            # Nuxt plugins
```

## Naming Conventions
- Composables: `use` prefix, camelCase → `useProducts.ts`, `useCart.ts`
- Components: PascalCase, grouped by feature → `components/pos/`, `components/product/`
- Pages: lowercase, index.vue for list pages → `pages/products/index.vue`
- Types: PascalCase interfaces → `Product`, `Order`, `CartItem`
- PocketBase collections: snake_case → `store_members`, `order_items`

## Composable Pattern
Every data composable follows this pattern:
1. Check `isOnline` from `useOnlineStatus()`
2. If online: call PocketBase SDK, cache result in Dexie
3. If offline or error: read from Dexie
4. For mutations: if online write to PB first, if offline add to syncQueue
5. Always include the `store` field from `useStore().activeStoreId`

## Currency
- All monetary values are in Thai Baht (THB)
- Format: `฿1,234.00` using `toLocaleString("th-TH", { minimumFractionDigits: 2 })`
